Version 1.0.0 BUCHANAN GENERATION, LLC MARKET RATE TARIFF
1. Availability. Buchanan Generation, LLC (???Buchanan???) makes electric energy and capacity available under this FERC electric tariff to any purchaser except as prohibited below. Applicant also makes the following ancillary services available to any purchaser except as prohibited below.
a. PJM. Buchanan offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10- minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. (???PJM???) and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection.
b. New York. Buchanan offers regulation and frequency response service, and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute non-synchronous, 10-minute operating reserves, 10-minute spinning reserves, and 10-minute non-spinning reserves) for sale to purchasers in the market administered by the New York Independent System Operator, Inc.
c. New England. Buchanan offers regulation and frequency response service (automatic generator control), operating reserve service (which includes 10 minute spinning reserve, 10-minute non-spinning reserve, and 30-minute operating reserve service) to purchasers within the markets administered by the ISO New England, Inc.
d. Third Party Ancillary Services. Buchanan offers Regulation Service, Energy Imbalance Service, Spinning Reserves, and Supplemental Reserves. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third party provider, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of a public utility affiliated with the third party provider; and (3) sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers.
2. Applicability. This Market Rate Tariff is applicable to all sales of electric energy and/or capacity by Buchanan not otherwise subject to a specific rate schedule or tariff.
3. Rates. All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Buchanan.
4. Other Terms and Conditions. All other terms and conditions of sale shall be established by agreement between Customer and Buchanan.
5. Compliance with Commission Regulations. Buchanan shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Buchanan???s market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Buchanan to engage in affiliate
sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits Buchanan???s market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Buchanan???s market-based rate authority, will constitute s violation of this tariff.
6. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority. Buchanan has been granted the following waivers and exemptions in connection with its market- based rate authority: (i) waiver of Subparts B and C of Part 35 regarding the filing of rate schedules, except Sections 35.12(a), 35.12(b), 35.15 and 35.16; (ii) waiver of the accounting and related reporting requirements under Parts 41, 101 and 141 of the Commission???s regulations; and (iii) blanket authorization under Section 204 of the Federal Power Act, 16 U.S.C. ?? 824c, and Part 34 of the Commission???s regulations to issue securities and assume obligations and liability. See Buchanan Generation, L.L.C., Letter Order, Docket No. ER02-1638-000 (May 29, 2002). Buchanan may sell available electric energy and/or capacity to Monongahela Power Company, The Potomac Edison Company, or West Penn Power Company (together ???Franchised Affiliates???) under the terms of this Rate Schedule, provided that the hourly rate for each transaction shall not exceed the hourly market price index in dollars per megawatt-hour as posted on the PJM homepage for transactions at the Allegheny Power/PJM transmission interface. See id. Hourly rates for all such sales shall be calculated as follows: (a) hourly values shall be calculated from the shortest duration PJM posting available (whenever that duration is not an hour) by dividing the number of period hours into the posted price; and (b) Buchanan will multiply all hourly prices within a calendar month as determined above by the megawatt-hours actually sold to arrive at a total rate for the month for all transactions. See id.
The Commission has also granted a waiver of affiliate restrictions in Section 35.39(c)(2)(i) of the Commission???s regulations, 18 CFR ?? 35.39(c)(2)(i), in order to permit FirstEnergy Solutions and its affiliates to share employees that engage in fuel procurement for generators owned by Solutions and its affiliates, including Buchannan Generation, and to permit the sharing of employees that engage in outage scheduling and economic dispatch at generating facilities that are jointly owned by AE Supply and Monongahela Power Company. FirstEnergy Corp., 136 FERC ?? 61,216 (2011).
7. Seller Category. Buchanan is a Category 1 Seller, as defined in 18 C.F.R. ?? 35.36(a), in the Central, Northwest, Southeast and Southwest Regions and in the Southwest Power Pool. Buchanan is a Category 2 seller, as defined in 18 C.F.R. ?? 35.36(a), in the Northeast Region.
8. Effective Date. This Market Rate Tariff is effective upon the date specified by the Commission.
SERVICE AGREEMENT
This Agreement is entered into this day of , 20 , by and among (???Buyer???) and Buchanan Generation, LLC (???Buchanan???) in consideration of the mutual covenants and agreements herein, Buyer and Buchanan the ???Party(ies)???) hereby agree as follows: Article 1. Service.
1.1 Buchanan agrees, during the term of this Agreement, to sell electric energy and/or capacity to Buyer and Buyer agrees to pay for such sale in accordance with Buchanan???s Market Rate Tariff on file with the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (???FERC???).
1.2 The terms and conditions of such service shall be (1) governed by the Market Rate Tariff, as it exists at the time of this Agreement or as subsequently amended, and (2) terms and conditions separately negotiated and agreed to by the Parties, with respect to sales of capacity, energy, and/or ancillary services to a Buyer under the Market Rate Tariff.
1.3 In executing this Agreement, neither Buchanan nor Buyer commits to enter into any individual sales of capacity, energy, and/or ancillary services to a Buyer under the Market Rate Tariff.
Article 2. Effective Date and Term of Agreement.
2.1 This Agreement shall become effective on the date first stated above. However, if the FERC or any reviewing court imposes any condition, limitation, or qualification under any of the provisions of the Federal Power Act which, individually or in the aggregate, Buchanan determines to be adverse to Buchanan, then Buchanan may at its option, terminate or renegotiate the terms of this Agreement in light of such FERC order or court action. Each party will use its best efforts to take, or cause to be taken, all actions requisite to obtain the necessary approvals so that this Agreement shall become effective as provided herein at the earliest practicable date.
2.2 This Agreement shall remain effective until terminated by either Party on written notice.
Article 3. Notice.
3.1 Any notice given pursuant to this Agreement or the Tariff shall he in writing and delivered or telecopied to the following:
If to Buchanan:
_______________________________
Phone: _______________ Fax: _________________
If to Buyer:
____________________________
3.2 The names and addresses for notice to either Party may be changed at any time by written notice to the other Party.
Article 4. Terms and Conditions.
4.1 This Service Agreement is subject to the Market Rate Tariff and any other terms and conditions agreed to by the parties which are hereby incorporated herein.
IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the Parties have caused this Service Agreement to he executed by their respective authorized officials as of the date first above written.
